<h2 id="what-kinds-of-writing-do-we-publish?">What kinds of writing do we publish?</h2>

<p>
  In addition to <a href="/events/">Events</a>, The A11Y Project features six main kinds of published content:
</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Posts</strong> are long form articles that discuss an aspect of accessibility in-depth. </li>
  <li><strong>Myths</strong> are short pieces that debunk common misconceptions and falsehoods about accessibility. </li>
  <li><strong>Quick tests</strong> outline a short collection of steps needed to check your content to determine if it is accessible.</li>
  <li><strong>Quick tips</strong> provide short, easy-to-digest and easy-to-implement accessibility-related information.</li>
  <li><strong>Assistive technology</strong> provides background information on the tools used by people who rely on them to navigate digital devices and interfaces.</li>
  <li><strong>How-tos</strong> are guides to implementing accessible code.</li>
</ul>

<p>
  Additionally, we have <a rel="external noopener" href="https://github.com/a11yproject/a11yproject.com/issues?q=is%3Aissue+is%3Aopen+sort%3Aupdated-desc">an Issue tracker</a> that lists different ongoing concerns and problems with the website.
</p>

<h2 id="our-audience">Our audience</h2>

<p>
  Our readers run the range from people who are completely new to the concept of accessibility to experienced practitioners who work full-time in the industry.
</p>

<p>
  Our content is written for people new to the industry. Because of this, we strive to keep our content short, easy to understand, and to the point. This serves everyoneâ€”sometimes people who have been doing accessibility work for a long time can benefit from a refresher!
</p>

<p>
  If you want to learn more about our writing standards, please read our <a href="/content-style-guide/">Content Style Guide</a>. This is the standard we'll be using four our editorial process.
</p>

<h2 id="what-will-we-need-from-you">What will we need from you?</h2>

<p>
  Interested in contributing? Great! Here's what you can provide to get things going.
</p>

<h3 id="if-you-have-a-github-account">If you have a GitHub account</h3>

<p>
  Submit an Issue with a suitable subject line. For example, content about the JAWS screen reader could be, "New assistive technology article about JAWS" somewhere in the subject. Please also be sure to select the <a rel="external noopener" href="https://github.com/a11yproject/a11yproject.com/labels/%5BContent%5D%20Article">"[Content] Article" Issue label</a>.
</p>

<h3 id="if-you-do-not-have-a-github-account">If you do not have a GitHub account</h3>

<p>
  Email hello@a11yproject.com with a suitable subject line that indicates the kind of content you are pitching.
</p>

<h3 id="editing">Editing</h3>

<p>
  Provide a link to your proposed content in a format that makes it easy to comment on and suggest edits to, such as a <a rel="external noopener" href="https://www.google.com/docs/about/">Google Doc</a> or <a rel="external noopener" href="https://www.dropbox.com/paper">Dropbox Paper</a> document.
</p>

<p>
  If you prefer not to use such a service, include your content as either an attachment or in the body of the email. If this process is used, edits will conducted via email replies.
</p>

<h2 id="what-well-provide">What we'll provide</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Polish.</strong> A thorough editorial process conducted by experienced web accessibility practitioners will help your content shine.</li>
  <li>
    <strong>Compensation.</strong> We value and respect your opinions and expertise. As such, we can offer payment for published content. Each article that has been reviewed and published will be paid $75.00 USD.
    <ul>
      <li>Payment will be conducted via PayPal. We are also willing to use other services, should circumstances require it.</li>
      <li>If you prefer, payment can be issued to a nonprofit of your choice instead. </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li><strong>Community.</strong> We will add you to a list of site contributors, including your website and social media information.</li>
  <li><strong>Promotion.</strong> We will <a rel="external noopener" href="https://twitter.com/A11YProject">promote your content on Twitter</a>. </li>
</ul>

